==English==

=== Alternative spellings ===
# crommulent

===Etymology===
A humorous [[neologism]] [[coin]]ed by television writer David X. Cohen for ''The Simpsons'' episode 3F13, "Lisa the Iconoclast".

===Adjective===
'''cromulent'''

# ''([[Nonce word]]):'' [[Fine]], [[acceptable]] or [[normal]].
#:''It's a perfectly '''cromulent''' word.'' — Ms. Hoover in ''The Simpsons''
# [[Excellent]], [[realistic]] or [[authentic]].
#:''He's [[embiggen]]ed that role with his '''cromulent''' performance.'' — Principal Skinner in ''The Simpsons''
Noun form: '''cromulence'''

